==English==

===Verb===
'''to [[sleep]] [[in]]'''
#{{intransitive}} {{idiom}} To sleep [[late]]; to go on sleeping past one's customary or planned hour.
#:''On a rainy Saturday, after a busy week at work, he closed the curtains and decided to '''sleep in'''.''

